//pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=60.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Misc / trivial balance issues</span><hr size=1> I realize these things aren't huge, but I really would like to see some of them go through as class/caster balance.<br>
<br>
I tried to put this off from other balance issues, because I consider them relatively trivial, but of some value day to day &quot;I enjoy playing this class&quot; value.<br>
<br>
I think they are changes that would have a minimal impact on balance of the game, result in a /shrug from other classes, and make life more enjoyable.<br>
<br>
-Up dodge cap a bit.<br>
-Up weapon caps back to at least something similar to what they were for parity pre kunark or at least a bit.<br>
-At least let us use some of the track sorting abilities.  I'm going to have the same information anyway.  Not having things sorted doesn't prevent me from seeing it, just makes it more inconvenient.  To me denying this ability is just frustrating.  I consider this a fair trade-off for ensnare.<br>
-Remove sit agro.  Because, simply it is just dumb, inneffective, and frustrating.  I can clearly not sit and avoid it, but why should I have to if that is part of my class.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uwytenk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>WyteNK</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Puppy</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#333399>(7/30/02 12:23:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=60.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Misc / trivial balance issues</span><hr size=1> Totally /agree with the Track Sorting.  That makes a ton of sense.  We can see all the mobs that we have on track regardless,  why not be able to sort them?  Not a biggie for me, but makes perfect sense.<br>
<br>
Wyte Psycnosis &lt;Ordo Malleus&gt;<br>
60 Dooid - Rallos Zek <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uoldoaktree.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Oldoaktree</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Finally Housebroken!</span><br>  Posts: 393<br> <font color=#333399>(7/30/02 11:34:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=60.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Misc / trivial balance issues</span><hr size=1> I actually disagree on track sorting.<br>
<br>
Before the ability to sort was added, there was no real measureable advantage for rangers with  track.  Sure, they could see the whole zone, but classes that had lower track caps actually had a more useful skill...because if we saw something on track it had to be relatively close.  A ranger just got a garbage list of every mob in zone.<br>
<br>
Rangers still rule the roost for checking rare spawns, but I would not take the advantage of sortable track away from them.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugeddine.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Geddine</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Puppy</span><br>  Posts: 78<br> <font color=#333399>(7/31/02 1:15:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=60.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Misc / trivial balance issues</span><hr size=1> Well the track list is actually sorted, but it is sorted in the order they spawned (but reversed at first entering the zone).<br>
<br>
