</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uglynna1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Glynna1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Puppy</span><br>  Posts: 69<br> <font color=#333399>(7/31/02 1:29:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=60.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Misc / trivial balance issues</span><hr size=1> I agree with Geddine on this one. Would be nice to sort mobs by alpha order and let Rangers keep their abilities. <p><img src=http://www.tchalla.net/Glynna.jpg><BR><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=32771 target=blank>Venerable Glynna Thunderrheart</a><BR>60th Hierophant of Tunare<BR>Mistress Fletcher 215<BR><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=128431 target=blank>Damari Castile</a><BR>41st Paladin<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/urolemeggido.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Role Meggido</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Might be Housebroken</span><br>  Posts: 202<br> <font color=#333399>(7/31/02 11:52:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=60.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Misc / trivial balance issues</span><hr size=1> My understanding when writing that part was that track skill determined the range that was tracked.  Track skill 125 might do range X but 250 might do something more like 2X.<br>
<br>
I felt and still feel that track-sort just arranges the information already available.<br>
<br>
The only distinction I can see is sort by distance, since that provides information not available in just scrolling through the list.  <br>
<br>
Mainly, I just throught we should get things we can basically already do:<br>
-Sorting by name<br>
-Sorting by level (con)<br>
<br>
Honestly though, I don't really see what difference it makes about distance.  The only place I can see distance ever being useful is in mowing down green cons.  In those situations distance really isn't that key, and a ranger is going to cut through green cons immensely easier than a druid anyway.<br>
<br>
